HEADWORD: Unprincipled
<hw>Un*prin"ci*pled</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Pref.
<ets>un-</ets> not + <ets>principled</ets>.]</ety> <def>Being without
principles; especially, being without right moral principles; also,
characterized by absence of principle.</def> --
<wordforms><wf>Un*prin"ci*pled*ness</wf>, <pos>n.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

